# type-scale
A Node.js library for dealing with HTML/CSS typographic scales

## Installation
```bash
npm install @ntdalbec/type-scale
```

## Usage
```javascript
const { TypeScale, Scale } = require("type-scale");

const scale = new TypeScale(Scale.MajorThird);

console.log(`\
h1: ${scale.h1}
h2: ${scale.h2}
h3: ${scale.h3}
h4: ${scale.h4}
h5: ${scale.h5}
h6: ${scale.h6}
`)

// expected:
// h1:   3.052em
// h2:   2.441em
// h3:   1.953em
// h4:   1.563em
// h5:   1.25em
// h6:   1em
// body: 1em
```

